dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v2.bswmoduletemplate.bswbehavior

Interface IBswModuleEntity

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IEntity, IExecutableEntity, IIdentifiable, IReferrable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IBswCalledEntity, IBswInterruptEntity, IBswSchedulableEntity

    public interface IBswModuleEntity
extends IEntity, IExecutableEntity
    IBswModuleEntity: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    Specifies the smallest code fragment which can be described for a BSW module or cluster within AUTOSAR.

    GENERATED CODE. DO NOT CHANGE!

      • getCalledEntrys

        java.util.Set<? extends IBswModuleEntry> getCalledEntrys()
        Query the undirectional to-many association CalledEntry.

        The entry of another (or the same) BSW module which is called by this entry (usually via C function call). This information allows to set up a model of call chains. The variablity of this association is especially targeted at debug scenarios: It is possible to have one variant calling into the AUTOSAR debug module and another one which doesn't. Note that this relation has been merked as obsolete, since the more powerful definition of a callPoint should be used.

        Returns:
        the referenced entities
        Throws:
        TresosDBException - in case of an error
